	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Sun Feb 03, 2013 2:18 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Zapper games not working</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In case it's an emulator: The Zapper doesn't need to see white. It can see any light color ($10, $21-$2C, $31-$3C) and still activate the photodiode. My test ROM <a href="http://pineight.com/nes/#ruder" class="postlink">Zap Ruder</a> tests this. Not having a Zapper plugged in at all shows up as continuously activating the sensor, and a game might read the sensor at the end of vblank and use that to tell whether the Zapper is plugged in.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


